      <h1 style="text-align: center;">Palakkad - The Gateway to Kerala</h1>
    <hr>
    
    <h2>About Palakkad</h2>
    <p>Palakkad, also known as the "Rice Bowl of Kerala," is a land of lush greenery, historical forts, and breathtaking landscapes.Palakkad is located at the foot of the Western Ghats and is a perfect blend of history, nature, and culture.</p>
    
    <h2>Tourist Attractions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Palakkad Fort</li>
        <li>Malampuzha Dam</li>
        <li>Silent Valley National Park</li>
        <li>Dhoni Waterfalls</li>
        <li>Nelliyampathy Hills</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Culture and Heritage</h2>
    <p>Palakkad is rich in cultural heritage, known for its classical music, traditional festivals, and vibrant temple arts.</p>
    
    <h2>Best Time to Visit</h2>
    <p>The best time to visit Palakkad is from September to March, when the weather is cool and pleasant.</p>
    
    <h2>How to Reach</h2>
    <p><strong>By Air:</strong> The nearest airport is Coimbatore International Airport.</p>
    <p><strong>By Train:</strong> Palakkad Junction and Palakkad Town Railway Stations connect the district to major cities.</p>
    <p><strong>By Road:</strong> Palakkad is well-connected by roads from major cities in Kerala and Tamil Nadu.</p>
    
    <h2>Contact Information</h2>
    <p>For more details, visit <a href="https://www.keralatourism.org/topic/palakkad">Tourism-Palakkad</a></p>
